stoprole.name: Stop-Role
stoprole.recommended:
**This is not required**

The Role which marks the end to the Separator Roles trigger.
If none is defined the Separator Role will work till the very top of the Role List

separator.name: Separator-Role
separator.recommended:
The Separator Role, it will be applied to Members if they fulfill following conditions:
**Self-Adapting `True`**: 
Looking at the Role list of the Server, the Separator Role will be applied if a Member gains any Role between the Seaprator and the Stop Role.
If no Stop Role is defined it stops at the top of the Role List.
Any Role moved between these 2 Roles or above the Separator Role will instantly start triggering the Separator Role

**Self-Adapting `False`**:
The Separator Role will be assinged to Members with at least one of the defined Roles

roles.name: Roles of this Separator
roles.recommended:
This is a Switch.
If the entered Role is already bypassed it will be removed.
Roles entered here will trigger the Separator Role

roleid.recommended: The Role which these Permissions will be applied to (Ayako internal only)

perms.name: Permissions of this Mod-Role
perms.answers: Select the Permissions in the Select Menu below
perms.recommended:
**Warning:**
Permissions Specified here will __overwrite Discord Role Permissions__
Meaning if the specified Mod-Role does not have the Permission to Ban Members on Discord, but does have this Permission here
Members with this Role __will be able to use Ayakos `ban` Command__ anyways

whitelistedroles.name: Whitelisted Roles
whitelistedroles.recommended:
This is a Switch.
If the entered Role is already whitelisted it will be removed.
If a Member has the Mod-Role, a Blacklisted Role __and__ a Whitelisted Role, they will be able to use the Mod-Roles Permissions

blacklistedroles.name: Blacklisted Roles
blacklistedroles.recommended:
This is a Switch.
If the entered Role is already blacklisted it will be removed.
If a Member has the Mod-Role __and__ a Blacklisted Role, they will __not__ be able to use the Mod-Roles Permissions

blacklistedusers.name: Blacklisted Users
blacklistedusers.recommended:
This is a Switch.
If the entered User is already blacklisted they will be removed.
If a User is blacklisted __and__ has the Mod-Role, they will __not__ be able to use the Mod-Roles Permissions

whitelistedusers.name: Whitelisted Users
whitelistedusers.recommended:
This is a Switch.
If the entered User is already whitelisted they will be removed.
If a User is whitelisted, has the Mod-Role __and__ has a Blacklisted Role, they will be able to use the Mod-Roles Permissions

blacklistedcommands.name: Blacklisted Commands
blacklistedcommands.recommended:
This is a Switch.
If the entered Comand is already blacklisted it will be removed.
If a Command is blacklisted __and__ would be allowed to be used according to the Mod-Role Permissions, it will __not__ be able to be used

whitelistedcommands.name: Whitelisted Commands
whitelistedcommands.recommended:
This is a Switch.
If the entered Comand is already whitelisted it will be removed.
If a Command is whitelisted __and__ would __not__ be allowed to be used according to the Mod-Role Permissions, it will be able to be used
